             (Police-constable E 49). I live at No.7, Bury-street, Bloomebury. On the 31st of January, about twenty minutes before six o'clock, I saw the prisoner in Regent-street begging; I searched him, and he gave me this pair of boots from his hat - he said a gentleman gave them to him for his wife.</p>
